This is one of the best 1911's ever IMO, personal defense and competition ready whatever is your purpose. I shot only 100 rounds of AE 230gr ball ammo through it  and hits a 15 yarder target with 1-1.5inch groupings. The stupidest thing I did and which some of us have committed is that idiot scratch, a tiny speck on the slide stop. Slide to frame fit is the tightest I've ever encountered in a 1911, well outside perhaps of Ed Browns, Les Baers and WC ( which I had not held) . Enough said, this is a COLT and no much introduction needed. I can meet and sell to buyers only after signing a transfer form after showing a TX DL or CHL. title: For Sale:  Custom Made Riggers Belts in Black or Coyote Broen
postcontent:
Let me make you the last belt you will ever need! Each belt is custom made to your specifications. If you have questions, please send me a message, I would be happy to answer them and make you the belt of your dreams! My goal is to provide you with a product that is extremely durable, reliable, and aesthetically pleasing at an incredible value. Because of this, I offer this belt in several configurations, so you only pay for the features you want.

I can meet you locally for the exchange, or ship it to you.  I will only ship if purchased through my Etsy store (https://www.etsy.com/listing/217188140/custom-riggers-belt-perfect-tactical?)  I ship to US addresses for $7.  I will not accept money orders, or anything like that.

First, a little bit about the materials:

The webbing is mil-spec, and is rated to a breaking strength of 6000 pounds. The buckle is specifically made to secure parachute straps, and is rated to 2500 pounds. Each belt is sewn on an industrial sewing machine using size 92 bonded nylon thread. The industry standard is size 69, but I kick it up a notch for better durability, strength, and just because I don't believe in doing things half-assed.

Each belt is made from a double layer of webbing, and reduced to a single layer right before the buckle. This provides rigidity and strength. This belt is great for attaching holsters, multi-tools, and drop leg rigs.

A little bit about the options:

Basic Riggers Belt ($22): Standard double layered belt. This includes a parachute grade buckle, and hook and loop velcro sewn onto the belt to keep the tail from dangling in the wind. This belt does not contain the V-ring like the belt shown in the picture.

V-Ring Belt ($29): This includes all the features of the standard belt, but with a V-ring for attaching accessories such as eye glass cases or water bottles. This is the V-Ring shown in the pictures. To keep the V-ring from dangling in the wind, I sew a retention strap made from 1 inch nylon webbing and hook and loop material.

Internal Loop Liner ($32): This includes all the features of the V-Ring Belt, but the entire inside is lined with loop velcro type material. The purpose of this is to mate with pouches, holsters, and accessories made for a duty belt, which have hook velcro type material on the mounting straps. This is the belt shown in the photographs.

Double Loop Liner ($35): Includes all the features of the Internal Loop Liner belt, but also has loop velcro type material on the outside of the belt. This is perfect if you intend on using this belt for the internal belt of a padded "war belt".

If there is something else you desire in a riggers belt, please let me know and I will add it as an option. I can do everything from putting soft loops in the side or back of the belt, adding additional d-rings, using a different buckle like the cobra buckle, and pretty much anything else you can dream up.

IMPORTANT NOTE REGARDING SIZING: To determine the size you need, measure one of the belts you currently wear from the end of the buckle to the hole you usually wear it in. The sizes here do not correspond to your pant size. The reason I use this method is because different manufacturers of pants size them differently. I know, it's weird, but that's what they do. Additionally, everyone wears their pants differently, resulting in a different belt size. The reason I use this method is to get you the belt in the exact size you want the first time.

My belts will adjust approximately 2 inches in from this size, and approximately 3 inches out from this size, similarly to a leather belt worn with the buckle in the middle hole.  If you need more or less, please let me know.
